## Overall

The shipped surface is honest about both what it catches (the
intended class — docs-vs-CLI drift in either direction, surfaced
with explicit drift-class semantics) and what it doesn't (drift
output is flag-only, not path+line; workflow dry-run wasn't
exercised on a real injected-drift PR). Both gaps are flagged as
v1.1 #2 follow-on work in CONTRACT rather than papered over.

The 16-entry initial allowlist is large but each entry has a
specific rationale tied to a real doc or contract reference, and
the entire surface is greppable from one file. The discipline
mechanism (mandatory expiry + frame-status resolution backstop)
ensures the allowlist cannot rot silently.

No concerns. **review.clean** against inner:b6c0c2f and the closure
follow-up commit that lands CHANGELOG + CONTRACT alongside this
review log.
